People are my passion. I like getting to know new people and their stories, and I LOVE photographing them. I guess you could say I am a people person with a photography habit.

My love affair with photography began when my grandparents bought me my first SLR camera for a birthday. I never saw the world the same again. Everything began appearing through the tiny rectangle of the viewfinder.

When I started traveling, my camera was my access to the local people and their culture. I told peoples stories through my photographs. I shared special moments with strangers with the clicking of my shutter. It always took a little time to get comfortable, but eventually people forgot about the camera and I captured their real personalities.

I still love people; I still travel; I still have my first camera; and I still have my photography habit. I get to capture the joy, the laughter, the love, the fun, and the poignant times in peoples lives everyday. The genuine and authentic moments are my favorites.

It is a dream-come-true to combine my passion for people with my love for photography and call it work.
